dataIdInfo.idPurp:
This dataset represents the polygons of the Exclusive Economic Zones (EEZ) of Kenya and Kenya counties, in a high resolution: the coastline is based on GSHHG (Global Self-consistent, Hierarchical, High-resolution Geography Database).
This dataset (the county EEZ territorial regions) is basically intended for research and academic purposes only.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Two GIS-cover in ESRI shape format were produced: one contains 12 nm mile polygon representing the county maritime boundaries; the second showing polygons representing the national EEZs from the 12nm mark to 200 nm. The 12 nm was constructed through buffering and clipping the national EEZ boundary were constructed. For the land-side border, parallel latitudinal lines were constructed and aggregated to derive five county 12 nm boundaries and polygons. A separate polygon was created for the EEZ (region beyond 12 nm) by erasing the 12 nm portion from the national EEZ to form the 6thregion
